version_description: The former best rated version is inaccurate.
Uses chords directly from the piano sheets.
I looked at other versions and the verse sounds more like the recorded song in my version.
This is the TOPxMM version of Tear In My Heart. I loved their collab with MUTEMATH so I decided to do the chords for that version since they're not out there.

My version uses a capo so that it has easier chords to play than other versions. I believe that mine is the most accurate on the pre-chorus. I have also spaced the chords accordingly with the lyrics so they are rhythmically easy to play while singing along.
It's an easier version and in a slightly different pitch than the original, have fun frens.
The tab was simplified and accuracy was added.
My version explains the intro and picking pattern of the verse and adds some new chords in the chorus and explains that you can use either the B or B7 chord in this song.
